### Task Management API Test Requests
### Use these requests in IntelliJ IDEA HTTP Client

### 1. Create a task
PUT http://localhost:8080/tasks
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "id": "123",
  "name": "Print Hello",
  "owner": "John Smith",
  "command": "echo Hello World!"
}

### 2. Create another task
PUT http://localhost:8080/tasks
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "id": "456",
  "name": "List Directory",
  "owner": "Jane Doe",
  "command": "dir"
}

### 3. Get all tasks
GET http://localhost:8080/tasks

### 4. Get task by ID
GET http://localhost:8080/tasks?id=123

### 5. Search tasks by name
GET http://localhost:8080/tasks/search?name=Hello

### 6. Execute task
PUT http://localhost:8080/tasks/123/execute

### 7. Execute another task
PUT http://localhost:8080/tasks/456/execute

### 8. Get all tasks (should show execution history)
GET http://localhost:8080/tasks

### 9. Test unsafe command (should fail)
PUT http://localhost:8080/tasks
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "id": "999",
  "name": "Dangerous Task",
  "owner": "Hacker",
  "command": "rm -rf /"
}

### 10. Delete a task
DELETE http://localhost:8080/tasks/123

### 11. Verify deletion
GET http://localhost:8080/tasks?id=123

### 12. Get all remaining tasks
GET http://localhost:8080/tasks
